// bug.md #70 (known_bugs_1.md, fixed): a local/parameter whose name shadows
// an in-scope namespace (`env`, `math`, ...), dynamically dispatched
// (interface-typed, forcing §3.4a's "always dispatch on runtime class"
// rule), calling a method that namespace ALSO declares as a free function
// with the same arity, used to silently resolve to the NAMESPACE function
// on --ir/native instead of the receiver's real runtime method. Root cause:
// Lower.cpp's NS::fn-call fallback checked only "does the callee's base
// text name a known namespace," with no check that the same name resolved
// to a local/parameter first — the fallback exists for unchecked prelude
// bodies (where e->resolved is genuinely null) but also fired whenever the
// CHECKER itself left e->resolved null for an unrelated reason (dynamic
// interface dispatch). Fixed by requiring the base name NOT be a local
// before taking the namespace fallback (same precedent as the `console`
// shadow guard a few lines above it in lowerCall).
interface IEnv { Array<string> args(); }
class FakeA : IEnv { Array<string> args() => ["A"]; }
class FakeB : IEnv { Array<string> args() => ["B", "extra"]; }

// The parameter is deliberately named `env` — the exact shadow shape bug
// #70 describes (§3.4a forces dynamic dispatch on an interface-typed
// receiver, and `env::args()` is a real prelude namespace function of the
// same arity).
string first(IEnv env) => env.args().at(0);

console.writeln(first(FakeA()));
console.writeln(first(FakeB()));

// A second shadowed name, exercised through a local variable rather than a
// parameter, and a different namespace (`math`) to confirm the fix isn't
// `env`-specific.
interface IMath { int value(); }
class FixedMath : IMath { int value() => 7; }
IMath math = FixedMath();
console.writeln(math.value().toString());
